                  <handDesc hands="2">
                     <handNote medium="ink">
                        <p>Nastaʻlīq in black ink, with headings, overlinings and
									punctuation marks in red, in two hands: <locus from="1v" to="441r">ff 1v-441r</locus>, with a few shikasta elements,
									copied by the author, <persName role="scr" key="person_f8383">ʻAbd al-Qādir ibn
										Sayyid ʻUmar Jīlānī al-Qādirī</persName>; <locus from="441r" to="465v">ff. 441r-465v</locus>, copied by a pupil or a
									disciple of the author with occasional misspellings. 
                        </p>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <p>Marginal corrections and additional references added in red. </p>
                     <p>A note on <locus n="1r">f. 1r</locus> introduces the author as the father of <persName>
									Sayyid Shāh Chirāgh Gīlānī</persName>, the author of a work
								called <title>Rawz̤ah-ʼi ʻAlīyah</title>. 
                     </p>
                     <p>A note by the second scribe on <locus n="441r">f. 441r</locus>, says that he started
								copying this book on <date calendar="Hijri qamari">5 Ramazan
									1142</date> (24 March 1730) in <placeName>Lahore</placeName>,
								due to the author, addressed as "ḥaz̤rat" losing his sight
								at the age of 82. 
                     </p>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
